      "content": "If your clients have natural textures, they should aim for styles that are impeccably maintained and polished, not necessarily completely straightened. The key is neatness; frizz or unkempt edges look unprofessional, regardless of the texture. They should ensure their hair is clean, well-shaped, and styled in a way that doesn't require constant adjustment during the meeting. A controlled silhouette always reads as more authoritative in a boardroom setting.",
